The project seeks to provide 9.6 gigawatts of nuclear power with a price tag of an estimated R1 trillion by 2030. CAPE TOWN - Eskom has delayed the release of its request for information (RFI) for the nuclear build programme.The utility was supposed to launch the RFI last week Thursday.The project seeks to provide 9.6 gigawatts of nuclear power with a price tag of an estimated R1 trillion by 2030.Eskom s Khulu Phasiwe says the RFI will be used to test the market . On Thursday the document team had to meet with the committee of the board so they can finalise everything and the next day was a public holiday. So between today and tomorrow it should be out on our website. 